1:
Have mercy on me, God, because of your covenant faithfulness;
\q for the sake of the multitude of your merciful actions, blot out my transgressions.
\q

4:
Against you, you only, I have sinned
\q and done what is evil in your sight;
\q you are right when you speak;
\q you are correct when you judge.

5:
See, I was born in iniquity;
\q as soon as my mother conceived me, I was in sin.
\q

7:
Purify me with hyssop, and I will be clean;
\q wash me, and I will be whiter than snow.
\q

18:
Do good in your good pleasure to Zion;
\q rebuild the walls of Jerusalem.
\q

19:
Then will you delight in the sacrifices of righteousness,
\q in burnt offerings and whole burnt offerings;
\q then our people will offer bulls on your altar.
